,0.00776145,-0.00878060,0.10313084,-0.01373954,0.01629339,-0.00889725,0.04737383,0.06284431,0.02672869,0.02779216,0.00707372,0.05302583,-0.03922321,-0.01126153,0.01973912,-0.01122776,0.03122398,-0.09008360,-0.01040119,-0.09122039,-0.01004037,-0.01426919,-0.10524249,-0.05294503,0.02138331,-0.01033412,-0.04300531,-0.01005511,-0.03688475,0.00400380,-0.05002785,-0.04839389,-0.00395487,0.02890858,-0.03408608,-0.07378022,0.01959337,0.01085887,0.01085031,0.03628715,0.01434995,-0.00469426]',E'Set up Absolute Imports and Module Path Aliases\n\nTo configure absolute imports, add the `baseUrl` configuration option to your `tsconfig.json` or `jsconfig.json` file. For example:\n\n```json filename="tsconfig.json or jsconfig.json"\n{\n  "compilerOptions": {\n    "baseUrl": "src/"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nIn addition to configuring the `baseUrl` path, you can use the `"paths"` option to `"alias"` module paths.\n\nFor example, the following configuration maps `@/components/*` to `components/*`:','{"source": "nextjs", "version": "15", "language": "typescript", "title": "01 Installationx", "section_title": "01-installationx", "url": "https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/01-getting-started/01-installation.mdx", "topics": "nextjs,react,ssr,01,installationx", "categories": "web,typescript,fullstack,ssr"}');
