0.19172965,0.03138689,0.01252362,0.09678771,0.02519109,0.02194756,0.05809356,0.07617186,-0.00316051,-0.05567362,0.06750844,0.01565798,-0.00930166,-0.01883838,-0.00520433,0.04470169,0.04406971,-0.03028019,-0.09098883,0.02812574,-0.01636216,0.02648075,0.02868821,-0.02325692,-0.03348507,-0.01564080,-0.00201681,-0.01875672,-0.03372514,-0.00894240,0.01738865,-0.00161119,0.00821508,0.04464832,0.04646144,-0.03549116,-0.03484158,0.04869319,0.04933675,-0.03972999,0.05303522,0.02236023,-0.01004965]',E'With an ORM or database\n\nSince Server Components are rendered on the server, credentials and query logic will not be included in the client bundle so you can safely make database queries using an ORM or database client.\n\n```tsx filename="app/blog/page.tsx" switcher\nimport { db, posts } from ''@/lib/db''\n\nexport default async function Page() {\n  const allPosts = await db.select().from(posts)\n  return (\n    <ul>\n      {allPosts.map((post) => (\n        <li key={post.id}>{post.title}</li>\n      ))}\n    </ul>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n```jsx filename="app/blog/page.js" switcher\nimport { db, posts } from ''@/lib/db''\n\nexport default async function Page() {\n  const allPosts = await db.select().from(posts)\n  return (\n    <ul>\n      {allPosts.map((post) => (\n        <li key={post.id}>{post.title}</li>\n      ))}\n    </ul>\n  )\n}\n```\n\nYou should still ensure requests are properly authenticated and authorized. For best practices on securing server-side data access, see the [data security guide](/docs/app/guides/data-security).','{"source": "nextjs", "version": "15", "language": "typescript", "title": "06 Fetching Datax", "section_title": "06-fetching-datax", "url": "https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/01-getting-started/06-fetching-data.mdx", "topics": "nextjs,react,ssr,06,fetching,datax", "categories": "web,typescript,fullstack,ssr"}');
